appname: 
appname: This is a PAM module for Linux authentication using USB memory sticks,
appname: SD cards, external SSD etc. Simply speaking, it lets you log onto
appname: your Linux user without typing password if the pre-configured memory
appname: stick is detected.
appname: 
appname: See https://github.com/mcdope/pam_usb for configuration instruction.
